{
  "stem": "11179.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We got some money from that account of my uncle to get us decent clothings and so on, for-- for which it had to-- it lasted us eight years, OK?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And things like that, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it wasn't-- it wasn't unlimited either, that account.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There wasn't that much there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had to pay round trip.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We didn't know why.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there's a book by David Kranzler, which is probably the best book writing about the Jews in Shanghai.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know if you want to take a picture of it later.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's an excellent, almost an historical book rather than a story.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- I-- and-- and the man did fantastic work on that book.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he probably much more objective than any of us who were there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because when you're in the middle of something, you're not as objective as when you do research like he did and got all kinds of information, and then got it pretty much the nail right on the head with whatever he says in that book.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have to-- nothing in for me, believe me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it is a good-- it is a good book to look it up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he says in that book, why.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The answer I found in that book.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I never knew why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Because the Jewish refugees came to Shanghai from the end of '38 already.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were a few that were there for years before-- I'm not talking about them-- from Germany and Austria.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Did any kind of work, including manual work, which was face losing for the Caucasians in Shanghai if you did work like the Chinese did, like the Chinese laborers or [INAUDIBLE] or craftsmen.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so they tried to stop that immigration.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
